      "message": "You\u0027re right, let me correct: i meant 4 values (int16_t each), so that\u0027s 8 bytes.\nThen at lines 113-124 you unpack with another 8bytes (but not always, note. Only if do_two \u003d1). This makes a total of 16bytes in a 256bit register. Pretty much what the SSE2 version is doing.\n\nTo take full advantage of AVX2, you should be doing four transforms at a time.",
